ow China's community and social problems threaten the ambitious nation's hopes for a prosperous and cohesive future. Lemos explains why protests will continue and a divided and self-serving leadership will not make people's dreams come true.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChongqing (China) -- Social conditions -- 21st century. 0aChongqing (China) -- Social life and customs -- 21st century. 0aNational characteristics, Chinese. 0aSocial change -- China -- Chongqing. 0aSocial changezChinazChongqing. 0aSocial stability -- China -- Chongqing. 0aSocial stabilityzChinazChongqing. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Customs & Traditions.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030017747340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300177473423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300177473/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles